<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The registerDojoStylesheet() method in Zend_Dojo_View_Helper_Dojo_Container, used only by Zend_Dojo_View_Helper_Editor, is unwanted by default and can adversely affect css styled pages.</p>

<p>The dojo.css stylesheet is not required for themeing. It acts more like YUI's reset.css, providing boilerplate styles. It can be safely omitted without affecting Zend_Dojo_View_Helper_Editor rendering (or any other dijit).</p>

<p>Workaround:
     Add the following to your view script AFTER creating the Zend_Dojo_View_Helper_Editor to disable importing dojo.css:</p>

<pre><code> &lt;?php $this-&gt;dojo()-&gt;registerDojoStylesheet(false); ?&gt;
</code></pre>

    </div>
